messages.message:
if the intended behavior isn't clear:

in the chatbot description example, we shouldnt let people click "create chatbot" if the description is too long

in the validation rule example we shouldnt let people click save when the threshold isn't an integer... we already check that its between 0 and 100 (I think after I provided similar feedback a long time ago) but I don't see how this can happen... presumably we use standard libraries / components that should provide this functionality ?
